<function>

access:   public

name: save

param: string, $event

param: string, $message

return: mixed

</function>

Saves (writes) an event and message to the log.

* Parameters:

 * string //$event//: The event type (typically 'debug', 'info', 'notice', 'severe', 'critical', etc).

 * string //$message//: A text description of the event.

* Returns mixed: Boolean false if the event was not saved, or a non-empty value if the event was saved (typically boolean true).

Saves (writes) an event and message to the log.

<code type="php">
// these are equivalent:
$log->save('info', 'informational message');
$log->save('critical', 'critical message');
$log->save('my special event type', 'describing the event');
</code>